oxford paravia italian dictionary , 2001 , isbn 0 - 19-860437-8   greece thumb|greek pastitsio the typical greek version has a bottom layer that is bucatini or other tubular pasta , with cheese and egg as a binder ; a middle layer of ground beef , veal or lamb with tomato and cinnamon , nutmeg or allspice ; another layer of pasta ; and a top layer of sauce , varying from an egg - based custard to a flour - based béchamel or a béchamel with cheese ( known as mornay sauce in france ) .

international cuisine : pastitsio , a popular noodle dish from this mediterranean country , may feature lamb or feta cheese

